      description:
        "### Monthly Earth Day Phangan \n\n**Introduction**\n\nMonthly Earth Day is an initiative launched by [Highly Artistic](https://x.com/highlyartistic?s=21). It’s not just an annual event but a global movement that ignites action on the 22nd of every month. It's a call to individuals worldwide to step out and make a tangible impact on our planet. From opting for reusable bags to planting trees, every action, big or small, contributes to a collective effort to enhance our world. Participants share their contributions on X, showcasing the power of united actions in fostering positive change.\n\nIn just one year, the community has grown to include hundreds of individuals, businesses, and projects globally, making remarkable strides in environmental and social impact. Together, participants have planted over 30,000 trees and removed more than 2,000 pounds of trash from natural spaces. Our efforts extend to education on composting, sustainable living, and even rewarding contributors with tokens and crypto for their positive impact.\n\nRegen Phangan Community, including [ReFi Phangan](https://x.com/ReFiPhangan?s=21) and [Green Pill Phangan](https://x.com/GreenPillKPG?s=21) are happy to support Monthly Earth Day (MED)  every 22nd of each month. Our first initiative - monthly cleanup with main stage and decentralized points of action, where every individual can participate no matter where they are. \n\n![Image](https://beige-defiant-spoonbill-537.mypinata.cloud/ipfs/QmXcjiexqmr66kFfSePnQnmDJhx2pj6qxjxjDiRPrRCS8v)\n\n### Grant Proposal\n\n**Objective:** MED Phangan seeks funding to support our environmental cleanup efforts. Our initiative aims to conduct monthly cleanups across the island, promoting ecological awareness and community engagement in environmental preservation.\n\n**Funding Needs:**\n\n1. **Materials:** Biodegradable bags and durable gloves for volunteers.\n2. **Logistics:** Rental of trucks for the transportation and proper disposal of collected waste.\n3. **Community Engagement:** Retroactive rewards and incentives for volunteers to boost participation and acknowledge their contributions.\n\n**Impact:**\n\n- **Environmental:** Reduce pollution and promote biodiversity on Phangan island.\n- **Social:** Foster a sense of community and environmental responsibility among participants.\n- **Education:** Increase awareness about waste management and environmental protection strategies.\n\n**Request:** We are seeking constant flow of income to fund monthly cleanups and reward the participation of volunteers. This investment in our environment will not only enhance the natural beauty of Phangan but also serve as a model for sustainable community engagement in environmental conservation efforts.\n\n**Conclusion:** With your support, we can continue to make significant strides in preserving the environment of Phangan. We believe that through collective action and dedicated funding, we can achieve a cleaner, greener future for our island and its inhabitants.\n",
